        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 12:05PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1205 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Carlsbad Caverns National Park, or 19 miles northeast
of Pine Springs, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Carlsbad Caverns National Park and Queen.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
